modules.description: Provides functions to access GitLab authentication token, base API URI, project name, and project ID. Works with strings for credentials and identifiers, and an integer for project identification. Used to configure API requests and fetch project-specific data from GitLab.

Provides functions to access notification service configuration values, including a authentication token, base URI, project name, and project ID. Works with string and integer types to support communication with external notification systems. Used to construct API requests and validate project-specific notification settings.

Handles exception capture and reporting with a standardized interface, enabling integration with issue tracking systems. Works with OCaml's exception types and custom reporter configurations. Used to automatically send stack traces and error details to bug trackers during unexpected failures in production code.

Handles configuration retrieval for notification services, exposing authentication tokens, base URIs, project names, and IDs. Supports string and integer operations to build API requests and validate project settings. Allows retrieval of specific configuration values and ensures consistency in external service interactions. Enables dynamic adjustment of notification parameters based on project requirements.
